<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>
A <rs type="material">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">lintel</rs> block with <rs type="decoration">egg and dart moulding</rs> above two stepped fasciae (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.75</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">4.95</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.95</measure>); the condition of the stone appears not to have altered since it was first recorded.</p></div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Texts</head>
<p>
i. is cut on the upper fascia, and ii. on the lower. A cross flanked by an <term lang="grc-Latn">alpha</term> and an <term lang="grc-Latn">omega</term> within a circle was later cut over i., probably at the time that ii. was cut, or perhaps when it was emended.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Description of Letters</head>

<p>
i. l. 1, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.07</measure>, l. 2, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.08</measure>; elongated, well-cut and regular; the <foreign lang="grc">Α</foreign> of <foreign lang="grc">ἡγεμόνα</foreign> was added above the line, <measure type="length" dim="height" value="0.03">0.03</measure>; scroll for abbreviation; b. <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre" precision="circa">0.04</measure>.

ii. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.07</measure>; well cut; abbreviations: last letter above line in <foreign lang="grc">ΜΗΤΡΟΠ<hi rend="superscript">ο</hi>, ΕΛΛΟΓΙΜ<hi rend="superscript">ο</hi>, ΣΧ<hi rend="superscript">ο</hi></foreign>; scroll in <foreign lang="grc"><expan><abbr>Φλ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">αουίου</supplied></expan>, <expan><abbr>κ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">αὶ</supplied></expan>, <expan><abbr>ἰνδ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ικτίωνος</supplied></expan></foreign>.</p>

</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>

<p>
i: <date notAfter="0370" exact="both" cert="low" notBefore="0365">A.D. 365/370</date>
(<rs type="criteria">titulature</rs>)
ii (and i.b): <date notAfter="0467" exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0434">Mid fifth century</date>
(<rs type="criteria">titulature</rs>, <rs type="criteria">prosopography</rs>).</p>

</div>
